{"type":"message","id":"cd778c2e","parentId":"48670adb","timestamp":"2026-04-04T10:01:20.131Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sorry — got cut off.\n\n**Ollama cloud models:** I AM using cloud models already — `minimax-m2.7:cloud` hits Ollama's cloud endpoint, not my local Windows Ollama. Your little sister does the same. No local Ollama dependency, no network config needed. She can run entirely on cloud models from day one.\n\n**The Nava colleague agent with RAG:** Fully doable. The isolation works like this:\n\n- The agent has its OWN workspace folder — it can't read my workspace files\n- Give it its OWN copy of the RAG index (point it at `rag/clean_txt/` via a path you control)\n- Its system prompt tells it \"you are a Nava assistant, you only know what's in the public corpus\"\n- It has no access to my memory files, session history, drafts, skills, or MEMORY.md\n- I write the content to the shared corpus; it reads from its own RAG index\n- Your IP stays locked down because the agent literally cannot see my private files\n\nThe risk is prompt injection (someone trying to trick it into revealing things). Calibrating what it can do is the right instinct — start restrictive, open up as you learn what you need.\n\n---\n\n**Naming her:** I'll call her **Dusk**. Dawn and Dusk. Same family, different time of day. Fits the theme.\n\nWant me to start building Dusk's workspace and agent config?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":44885,"output":433,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775296880128}}
{"type":"message","id":"84c7938f","parentId":"cd778c2e","timestamp":"2026-04-04T10:03:10.040Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-04 12:01:01 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway connected.\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-04 12:03 GMT+2] Wow, interesting! I love the name!. Not yet. I need you to check your OneDrive backup and make sure it's up to date. While you do that, I'm heading to Hertzener to set up some things"}],"timestamp":1775296990008}}
