{"type":"message","id":"11a657c0","parentId":"63d786ce","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:03:48.100Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now writing the instructions and git repo notes.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_59a06d08-ad16-4880-8e3d-fae35f8e80e4","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Apps/Dawn-Restore/RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md","content":"# Dawn Restore Instructions — Fresh Machine Setup\n\n## What This Is\nFull backup of Dawn (OpenClaw AI assistant) workspace and configuration.\nRestore to a new Windows machine with WSL2 and Ollama installed.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Base Infrastructure\n\n### 1.1 Enable WSL2\nRun PowerShell as Administrator:\n```powershell\nwsl --install\n```\nRestart machine when prompted.\n\n### 1.2 Install Ubuntu 24.04 LTS from Microsoft Store\nAfter install, set up your Linux user:\n```bash\n# Create user with sudo access\nsudo adduser tiny\nsudo usermod -aG sudo tiny\n# Switch to tiny user\nsu - tiny\n```\n\n### 1.3 Install Ollama\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\n```\n**On Windows:** Download from https://ollama.com/download/windows — Ollama runs natively on Windows now, no WSL required. After installing, verify:\n```bash\nollama list\n```\nPull models used by Dawn:\n```bash\nollama pull minimax-m2.7\nollama pull minimax-m2.7:cloud\nollama pull gemma3:27b\nollama pull llama3.2:3b\nollama pull nemotron-3-super\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: OpenClaw Installation\n\n### 2.1 Install Node.js 20.x\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -\nsudo apt-get install -y nodejs\nnode --version  # should be v20.x.x\n```\n\n### 2.2 Install OpenClaw\n```bash\nsudo npm install -g openclaw\n```\n\n### 2.3 Install Skills\n```bash\nopenclaw skills install clawhub healthcheck mcporter node-connect session-logs skill-creator tmux weather\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Restore Configuration\n\n### 3.1 Restore openclaw.json\nCopy `openclaw.json` from this backup to `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`:\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw\ncp /path/to/backup/openclaw.json ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n```\n**Edit the file** and update:\n- Gateway port (if different)\n- Any absolute paths that changed\n- WhatsApp credentials (re-auth may be needed)\n- Ollama endpoint (http://localhost:11434 or Windows IP)\n\n### 3.2 Restore Workspace\n```bash\ncp -r workspace_backup/* ~/.openclaw/workspace/\n```\nOr copy the entire `workspace_backup/` folder to `~/.openclaw/workspace/` via Windows File Explorer.\n\n### 3.3 OpenClaw Configuration Check\n```bash\n# Test configuration\nopenclaw status\n# View config\nopenclaw config show\n```\n\n### 3.4 Gateway Token\nThe saved openclaw.json uses token \"ollame\" (shortened from \"ollama\"). \n**Update the token in openclaw.json** to match your gateway token after first start.\nFind it in the gateway startup output or in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: First Boot\n\n### 4.1 Start OpenClaw Gateway\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway start\nopenclaw gateway status\n```\nIf gateway fails, check logs:\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway logs\n```\n\n### 4.2 Connect to OpenClaw\nOpen a new terminal:\n```bash\nopenclaw tui\n```\nOr connect via web UI at `http://localhost:18789`\n\n### 4.3 Verify Ollama Connection\nInside OpenClaw:\n```\n/model ollama list\n```\nShould show all pulled models. If Ollama isn't reachable:\n- Check that Ollama is running: `ollama serve` (Windows) or check service status\n- Update openclaw.json `ollama_endpoint` to correct address\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Git Repository\n\n### 5.1 Clone the Repo\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit remote set-url origin <your-git-origin-url>\ngit pull origin master\n```\nOr if setting up fresh:\n```bash\ngit init\ngit remote add origin <your-git-origin-url>\ngit pull origin master\n```\n\n### 5.2 Git Log Reference\nLast commit before backup: `47b10e3`\nSee `GIT_REPO.md` in this folder for full branch history and remote configuration.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Windows-Specific Setup\n\n### 6.1 Screenshot Folders (for Tiny's workflow)\nCreate these folders manually or copy from backup:\n```\nC:\\Users\\Tiny4Lurv\\OpenClawScreenshots\\\nC:\\Users\\Tiny4Lurv\\OneDrive\\Pictures\\Screenshots 1\\\n```\n\n### 6.2 Visible Browser (WSLg)\nIf using WSLg with visible Chromium:\n```bash\nexport DISPLAY=:0\nexport ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto\nnohup /usr/bin/chromium-browser \\\n  --no-sandbox \\\n  --remote-debugging-port=18801 \\\n  --user-data-dir=/tmp/chromium-visible \\\n  > /tmp/chromium_visible.log 2>&1 &\n```\n\n### 6.3 LinkedIn Browser Profile\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw/browser_profiles/linkedin_tiny\n```\nRestore from backup if profile data exists.\n\n---\n\n## Critical Reminders\n\n1. **Token:** Update `openclaw.json` token before first gateway start\n2. **Ollama:** Must be running and models pulled before first chat\n3. **WhatsApp:** May need re-authentication via QR code\n4. **Paths:** All absolute paths in openclaw.json need updating for new machine\n5. **WSLg:** Only works if WSLg is enabled (install with `wsl --install` defaults to enabling it)\n\n---\n\n## After Restore Checklist\n\n- [ ] Gateway starts without errors\n- [ ] Ollama models respond (`/model` test)\n- [ ] WhatsApp connected (scan QR if needed)\n- [ ] Workspace files present (`ls ~/.openclaw/workspace`)\n- [ ] Memory files present (`ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory`)\n- [ ] Git remote set and pulling\n- [ ] Skills installed (`openclaw skills list`)\n\n---\n\n## File Inventory in This Backup\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `openclaw.json` | OpenClaw configuration |\n| `memory_backup/` | All memory files (Mar 10 - Apr 5) |\n| `workspace_backup/` | Full workspace (memory excluded) |\n| `RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md` | This file |\n| `GIT_REPO.md` | Git history and remote info |\n\n**Not included** (generated fresh on restore):\n- Browser profiles (too large + session-specific)\n- Playwright cache\n- rag/.venv (Python virtual environment — rebuild with `pip install -r rag/requirements.txt`)\n- node_modules (reinstalled by npm)\n- .git (full repo cloned from remote)\n"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":53138,"output":1584,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775347428098}}
